{"title_page": "The Nat King Cole Story", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = The Nat King Cole Story\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Nat King Cole]]\n| cover      = natstory.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1961\n| recorded   = (original recordings) - January 30, May 6, September 30, 1958, April 1959, March 1, 1960<br>(new recordings) - March 22\u201324, 27, 29-30, April 3, July 6, 19-20, 1961<ref>{{cite web |url=http://apileocole.alongthehall.com/releases/album20.html |title=A Pile o' Cole's Nat King Cole website - The Nat 'King' Cole Story |publisher=Apileocole.alongthehall.com |accessdate=2012-01-07}}</ref>\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Traditional pop music]], [[vocal jazz]]\n| length     = 103:45\n| label      = [[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n| producer   = Lee Gillette\n| prev_title = [[The Magic of Christmas (Nat King Cole album)|The Magic of Christmas]]\n| prev_year  = 1960\n| next_title = [[The Touch of Your Lips (album)|The Touch of Your Lips]]\n| next_year  = 1961\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = The Nat King Cole Story\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Nature Boy]]\n | single1date = March 29, 1948\n}}\n}}\n{{Album reviews\n|rev1 = [[Allmusic]]\n|rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=allmusic>[{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r60906|pure_url=yes}} Allmusic review]</ref>\n|rev2 = ''[[The Rolling Stone Jazz Record Guide]]''\n| rev2Score = {{rating|3|5}}<ref name=RSJRG>{{Cite book\n |editor-last=Swenson\n |editor-first=J.\n | author-link = \n | year = 1985\n | title = The Rolling Stone Jazz Record Guide\n | publisher = Random House/Rolling Stone\n | location = USA\n | isbn = 0-394-72643-X\n | pages = 44\n}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''The Nat King Cole Story''''' is a 1961 [[album]] by [[Nat King Cole]]. The album was a retrospective of Cole's recording career, designed to present many of his earlier hits in new recordings featuring [[stereophonic sound|stereo]] sound. Cole is accompanied on the re-recordings by many of the notable arrangers and bands that had appeared with him on the original records.<ref name=allmusic />\n\nOf particular note is Cole's re-recording of \"[[The Christmas Song]]\". This was Cole's fourth, and final, recording of the song, and also the first version recorded in stereo. This recording of the song was subsequently added to a 1963 reissue of Cole's 1960 LP ''[[The Magic of Christmas (Nat King Cole album)|The Magic of Christmas]]'' (the album concurrently retitled ''The Christmas Song'' and given new cover art), and remains one of Cole's best-known recordings and among the most-played Christmas tunes on radio each December.\n\nAt the [[4th Grammy Awards]], ''The Nat King Cole Story'' was nominated for the [[Grammy Award for Album of the Year]].\n\n== Track listing ==\nDisc 1\n# \"[[Straighten Up and Fly Right]]\" ([[Nat King Cole]], [[Irving Mills]]) \u2013 2:36\n# \"[[Sweet Lorraine]]\" ([[Cliff Burwell]], [[Mitchell Parish]]) \u2013 3:22\n# \"[[It's Only a Paper Moon]]\" ([[Harold Arlen]], [[Yip Harburg]], [[Billy Rose]]) \u2013 2:57\n# \"[[Route 66 (song)|(Get Your Kicks on) Route 66]]\" ([[Bobby Troup]]) \u2013 2:56\n# \"[[(I Love You) For Sentimental Reasons]]\" (William Best, Deek Watson) \u2013 3:04\n# \"[[The Christmas Song|The Christmas Song (Merry Christmas to You)]]\" ([[Mel Torm\u00e9]], [[Robert Wells (songwriter)|Robert Wells]]) \u2013 3:11\n# \"[[Nature Boy]]\" ([[eden ahbez|Eden Ahbez]]) \u2013 2:53\n# \"[[Lush Life (jazz song)|Lush Life]]\" ([[Billy Strayhorn]]) \u2013 3:46\n# \"Calypso Blues\" (Cole, D.W. George) \u2013 3:25\n# \"[[Mona Lisa (Nat King Cole song)|Mona Lisa]]\" ([[Ray Evans]], [[Jay Livingston]]) \u2013 3:27\n# \"[[Orange Colored Sky]]\" ([[Milton DeLugg]], [[Willie Stein]]) \u2013 2:33\n# \"[[Too Young (Sidney Lippman and Sylvia Dee song)|Too Young]]\" ([[Sylvia Dee]], [[Sidney Lippman]]) \u2013 3:24\n# \"[[Unforgettable (Nat King Cole song)|Unforgettable]]\" ([[Irving Gordon]]) \u2013 3:27\n# \"[[Somewhere Along the Way]]\" ([[Jimmy Van Heusen|Kurt Adams]], [[Sammy Gallop]]) \u2013 3:00\n# \"[[Walkin' My Baby Back Home (song)|Walkin' My Baby Back Home]]\" ([[Fred E. Ahlert]], [[Roy Turk]]) \u2013 2:42\n# \"[[Pretend (song)|Pretend]]\" ([[Lew Douglas]], Dan Belloc, Frank LaVere, Cliff Parman) \u2013 2:45\n# \"Blue Gardenia\" (Lester Lee, [[Bob Russell (songwriter)|Bob Russell]]) \u2013 3:04\n# \"[[I Am in Love]]\" ([[Cole Porter]]) \u2013 2:33\nDisc 2\n# \"[[Answer Me, My Love]]\" ([[Fred Rauch]], [[Carl Sigman]], [[Gerhard Winkler (composer)|Gerhard Winkler]]) \u2013 2:56\n# \"[[Smile (Charlie Chaplin song)|Smile]]\" ([[Charlie Chaplin]], [[Geoffrey Parsons (lyricist)|Geoff Parsons]], [[John Turner (lyricist)|John Turner]]) \u2013 2:53\n# \"[[Darling, Je Vous Aime Beaucoup]]\" ([[Anna Sosenko]]) \u2013 2:48\n# \"The Sand and the Sea\" (Cole, Hester) \u2013 2:41\n# \"If I May\" ([[Rose Marie McCoy]], [[Charles Singleton (songwriter)|Charles Singleton]]) \u2013 2:57\n# \"[[A Blossom Fell]]\" (Howard Barnes, Harold Cornelius, Dominic John) \u2013 2:41\n# \"[[To the Ends of the Earth (Nat King Cole song)|To the Ends of the Earth]]\" ([[Noel Sherman]], [[Joe Sherman (songwriter)|Joe Sherman]]) \u2013 2:25\n# \"[[Night Lights (Nat King Cole song)|Night Lights]]\" (Gallop, [[Chester Conn]]) \u2013 2:48\n# \"[[Ballerina (Sidney Keith Russell and Carl Sigman song)|Ballerina]]\" (Sigman, [[Bob Russell (songwriter)|Bob Russell]]) \u2013 2:41\n# \"[[Stardust (1927 song)|Stardust]]\" (Parish, [[Hoagy Carmichael]]) \u2013 3:14\n# \"[[Send for Me (song)|Send for Me]]\" (Ollie Jones) \u2013 2:30\n# \"[[Saint Louis Blues (song)|St. Louis Blues]]\" ([[W. C. Handy]]) \u2013 2:25\n# \"Looking Back\" ([[Brook Benton]], [[Belford Hendricks]], [[Clyde Otis]]) \u2013 2:26\n# \"[[Non Dimenticar]]\" (Shelly Dobbins, Michele Galdieri, [[Gino Redi]]) \u2013 3:07\n# \"[[Paradise (1931 song)|Paradise]]\" ([[Nacio Herb Brown]], [[Gordon Clifford (lyricist)|Gordon Clifford]]) \u2013 3:11\n# \"[[Mary Don't You Weep|Oh Mary, Don't You Weep]]\" ([[Spiritual (music)|African-American Spiritual]] adapted by Nat King Cole & [[Gordon Jenkins]]) \u2013 1:55\n# \"Ay, Cosita Linda\" ([[Pacho Galan]]) \u2013 2:14\n# \"Wild Is Love\" ([[Raymond Rasch|Ray Rasch]], Dotty Wayne) \u2013 2:48\n\n== 2011 reissue ==\nIn 2011, the [[Analogue Productions]] label reissued the album as a 2-disc hybrid [[Super Audio CD|SACD]] set and a 5-disc 45 rpm vinyl set. Both versions feature a new stereo mix of the entire album by [[Steve Hoffman (audio engineer)|Steve Hoffman]] and Kevin Gray, while the SACD also includes a discrete three-channel mix of most songs. Two bonus tracks (\"[[Ramblin' Rose]]\" and \"Those Lazy-Hazy-Crazy Days of Summer\") are also included on both versions.\n\n== Personnel ==\n=== Performance ===\n* [[Nat King Cole]] - [[singing|vocals]] (1.01-05, 1.08, 1.11, 1.15, 1.18, 2.09, 2.12, 2.15, [[Lead vocalist|lead]] on 1.06-07, 1.09-10, 1.12-14, 1.16-17, 2.01-08, 2.11, 2.13-14, 2.16-18), [[piano]] (1.01-05)\n* Dale Anderson - [[Percussion instrument|percussion]] (1.08-09, 1.15, 1.17-18, 2.07-09, 2.14)\n* George Acevedo - percussion (1.11)<ref name=\"Orange\">{{cite web |url=https://www.jazzdisco.org/nat-king-cole/discography/#610706 |author=Nat King Cole with Stan Kenton\u2019s Orchestra |title=Orange Colored Sky |publisher=Capitol |date=6 July 1961}}</ref>\n* [[Everett Barksdale]] - [[guitar]] (2.05, 2.11, 2.13)<ref name=\"Send\">{{cite web |url=https://www.jazzdisco.org/nat-king-cole/discography/#610403 |author=Nat King Cole with Ralph Carmichael\u2019s Orchestra |title=Send for Me, etc. |publisher=Capitol |date=3 April 1961}}</ref>\n* [[Larry Bunker]] - percussion (1.11)<ref name=\"Orange\"/>\n* [[Kenny Burrell]] - guitar (2.05, 2.11, 2.13)<ref name=\"Send\"/>\n* [[John Collins (jazz guitarist)|John Collins]] - guitar (1.01-07, 1.10, 1.12-14, 1.16, 2.01-06, 2.11-13, 2.15, 2.17-18)\n* [[Joe Comfort]] - [[Double bass|bass played by]] (1.08-09, 1.11, 1.15, 1.17-18, 2.07-09, 2.14)\n* Rene Faure - piano (2.15)<ref name=\"Blame\">{{cite web |url=https://www.jazzdisco.org/nat-king-cole/discography/#580506 |author=Nat King Cole with Gordon Jenkins\u2019 Orchestra |title=Don\u2019t Blame Me, etc. |publisher=Capitol |date=6 May 1958}}</ref>\n* [[First Church of Deliverance|First Church of Deliverance Choir]] - [[Backing vocalist|background vocals]] (2.16)<ref name=\"WarStudy\">{{cite web |url=https://www.jazzdisco.org/nat-king-cole/discography/#580929 |author=Nat King Cole with the First Church of Deliverance Choir |title=Ain\u2019t Gonna Study War No More, etc. |publisher=Capitol |date=29 September 1958}}</ref><ref name=\"Pray\">{{cite web |url=https://www.jazzdisco.org/nat-king-cole/discography/#580930 |author=Nat King Cole with the First Church of Deliverance Choir |title=I Couldn\u2019t Hear Nobody Pray, etc. |publisher=Capitol |date=30 September 1958}}</ref>\n* [[Charlie Harris]] - bass played by (1.01-07, 1.10, 1.12-14, 1.16, 2.01-04, 2.06, 2.12, 2.15, 2.17-18)\n* Ernie Hayes - piano (2.05, 2.11, 2.13)<ref name=\"Send\"/>\n* [[Al Hendrickson]] - guitar (1.09, 1.11, 1.17, 2.07-08, 2.14)\n* Irakitan Trio - background vocals (2.17)<ref name=\"SpanishNat\">{{cite web |url=https://www.jazzdisco.org/nat-king-cole/discography/#590413 |author=Nat King Cole with Dave Cavanaugh\u2019s Orchestra |title=Perfidia (Spanish), etc. |publisher=Capitol |date=April 1959}}</ref>\n* [[Hank Jones]] - piano (1.06-07, 1.10, 1.13, 2.04, 2.06)\n* [[Lou Levy (pianist)|Lou Levy]] - piano (2.18)<ref name=\"Wildlove\">{{cite web |url=https://www.jazzdisco.org/nat-king-cole/discography/#600301 |author=Nat King Cole with Nelson Riddle\u2019s Orchestra |title=Wild is Love, etc. |publisher=Capitol |date=1 March 1960}}</ref>\n* Jerry MacKenzie - [[Drum kit|drums]] (1.11)<ref name=\"Orange\"/>\n* [[Red Mitchell]] - bass played by (1.11)<ref name=\"Orange\"/>\n* Mike Pacheco - percussion (1.09, 1.17, 2.07-08, 2.14)\n* Milton Raskin - piano (1.08-09, 1.15, 1.17-18, 2.07-09, 2.14)\n* [[Alvino Rey]] - guitar (1.08-09, 1.15, 1.17-18, 2.07-09, 2.14)\n* [[Emil Richards]] - percussion (2.18)\n* [[Paul Smith (pianist)|Paul Smith]] - piano (1.11)<ref name=\"Orange\"/>\n* [[Sylvia Telles]] - additional lead vocals (2.17)<ref name=\"SpanishNat\"/>\n* [[Lee Young]] - drums (1.06-18, 2.01-09, 2.11-15, 2.17-18)\n\n=== Production ===\n* Nat King Cole - choir arranger, [[Arrangement|arranger]] (1.01-05) (2.16)\n* [[Ralph Carmichael]] - arranger, [[conducting|conductor]] (1.06-10, 1.12-18, 2.01-09, 2.11, 2.13-14)\n* [[Dave Cavanaugh]] - arranger, conductor (2.17)<ref name=\"SpanishNat\"/>\n* [[Gordon Jenkins]] - music arranger, orchestra conductor (2.15),<ref name=\"Blame\"/> choir arranger, choir conductor (2.16)<ref name=\"WarStudy\"/><ref name=\"Pray\"/>\n* [[Stan Kenton]] - conductor (1.11)\n* [[Billy May]] - arranger, conductor (1.15)\n* [[Nelson Riddle]] - arranger, conductor (2.12, 2.18)<ref name=\"Wildlove\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.jazzdisco.org/nat-king-cole/discography/#580129 |author=Nat King Cole with Nelson Riddle\u2019s Orchestra |title=Beale Street Blues, etc. |publisher=Capitol |date=29 January 1958}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.jazzdisco.org/nat-king-cole/discography/#580130 |author=Nat King Cole with Nelson Riddle\u2019s Orchestra |title=\"Morning Star\", etc. |publisher=Capitol |date=30 January 1958}}</ref>\n* [[Pete Rugolo]] - arranger (1.08)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Nat King Cole}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nat King Cole Story, The}}\n[[Category:1961 albums]]\n[[Category:Nat King Cole albums]]\n[[Category:Capitol Records albums]]\n[[Category:Albums arranged by Ralph Carmichael]]\n[[Category:Albums conducted by Ralph Carmichael]]\n[[Category:Albums arranged by Billy May]]\n[[Category:Albums conducted by Billy May]]\n[[Category:Albums conducted by Stan Kenton]]\n[[Category:Albums arranged by Nelson Riddle]]\n[[Category:Albums arranged by Pete Rugolo]]\n[[Category:Albums arranged by Frank De Vol]]\n", "text_old":