{"title_page": "Alasdair Fotheringham", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2016}}\n'''Alasdair Fotheringham''' is a British foreign affairs and sports [[journalist]], specializing in [[cycle racing]]. Based in [[Spain]], Fotheringham works as a freelance journalist and has written articles for ''[[The Independent]]'', ''[[The Independent On Sunday]]'', ''[[The Guardian]]'', ''[[The Daily Express]]'', ''[[The Sunday Express]]'', ''[[Cycling Weekly]]'' and [[Reuters]].<ref name=\"extratime\">{{cite news|url=http://blogs.independent.co.uk/extratime/alasdair-fotheringham.html |title=Extra Time: Alasdair Fotheringham |publisher=The Independent |accessdate=2008-11-08 |location=London |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081202185940/http://blogs.independent.co.uk/extratime/alasdair-fotheringham.html |archivedate=2 December 2008 }}</ref> He has been The Independent's cycling correspondent since 2001, and having covered the [[Tour de France]] 17 times, Fotheringham covered the [[2008 Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]] for the first time in 2008.<ref name=\"extratime\" /> He is the brother of fellow cycling journalist [[William Fotheringham]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rouleurmagazine.wordpress.com/2012/07/04/on-the-shelf/ |title=On the Shelf |last1=Cleverly |first1=Ian |date=4 July 2012 |website=[[Rouleur (magazine)|Rouleur]] |accessdate=16 April 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Books==\n*{{cite book| title=The Eagle of Toledo: The Life and Times of Federico Bahamontes| publisher=[[Aurum Press]]| year= 2012| isbn=978-1-8451-3700-7}}<ref name=\"Eagle of Toledo review\">{{cite web| url=http://www.podiumcafe.com/2012/9/24/3383814/the-eagle-of-toledo-by-alasdair-fotheringham| title=Eagle of Toledo Review| publisher=Podium Caf\u00e9}}</ref>\n*{{cite book| title=Reckless: The Life and Times of Luis Oca\u00f1a| publisher=[[Bloomsbury Sport]]| year= 2014| isbn=978-1-4088-4602-5}}<ref name=\"Reckless review\">{{cite web| url=http://www.podiumcafe.com/book-corner/2014/7/19/5917899/reckless-by-alasdair-fotheringham| title=Reckless Review| publisher=Podium Caf\u00e9}}</ref>\n*{{cite book| title=The End of the Road: The Festina Affair and the Tour that Almost Wrecked Cycling| publisher=[[Bloomsbury Sport]]| year= 2015| isbn=978-1-4729-1302-9}}<ref name=\"The End of the Road review\">{{cite web| url=http://www.podiumcafe.com/book-corner/2016/8/21/12573418/the-end-of-the-road-by-alasdair-fotheringham| title=The End of the Road Review| publisher=Podium Caf\u00e9}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fotheringham, Alasdair}}\n[[Category:Cycling journalists]]\n[[Category:British male journalists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{UK-journalist-stub}}\n{{UK-cycling-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2016}}\n'''Alasdair Fotheringham''' is a British foreign affairs and sports [[journalist]], specializing in [[cycle racing]]. Based in [[Spain]], Fotheringham works as a freelance journalist and has written articles for ''[[The Independent]]'', ''[[The Independent On Sunday]]'', ''[[The Guardian]]'', ''[[The Daily Express]]'', ''[[The Sunday Express]]'', ''[[Cycling Weekly]]'' and [[Reuters]].<ref name=\"extratime\">{{cite news|url=http://blogs.independent.co.uk/extratime/alasdair-fotheringham.html |title=Extra Time: Alasdair Fotheringham |publisher=The Independent |accessdate=2008-11-08 |location=London |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081202185940/http://blogs.independent.co.uk/extratime/alasdair-fotheringham.html |archivedate=2 December 2008 }}</ref> He has been The Independent's cycling correspondent since 2001, and having covered the [[Tour de France]] 17 times, Fotheringham covered the [[2008 Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]] for the first time in 2008.<ref name=\"extratime\" /> He is the brother of fellow cycling journalist [[William Fotheringham]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rouleurmagazine.wordpress.com/2012/07/04/on-the-shelf/ |title=On the Shelf |last1=Cleverly |first1=Ian |date=4 July 2012 |website=[[Rouleur (magazine)|Rouleur]] |accessdate=16 April 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Books==\n*{{cite book| title=The Eagle of Toledo: The Life and Times of Federico Bahamontes| publisher=[[Aurum Press]]| year= 2012| isbn=978-1-8451-3700-7}}<ref name=\"Eagle of Toledo review\">{{cite web| url=http://www.podiumcafe.com/2012/9/24/3383814/the-eagle-of-toledo-by-alasdair-fotheringham| title=Eagle of Toledo Review| publisher=Podium Caf\u00e9}}</ref>\n*{{cite book| title=Reckless: The Life and Times of Luis Oca\u00f1a| publisher=[[Bloomsbury Sport]]| year= 2014| isbn=978-1-4088-4602-5}}<ref name=\"Reckless review\">{{cite web| url=http://www.podiumcafe.com/book-corner/2014/7/19/5917899/reckless-by-alasdair-fotheringham| title=Reckless Review| publisher=Podium Caf\u00e9}}</ref>\n*{{cite book| title=The End of the Road: The Festina Affair and the Tour that Almost Wrecked Cycling| publisher=[[Bloomsbury Sport]]| year= 2015| isbn=978-1-4729-1302-9}}<ref name=\"The End of the Road review\">{{cite web| url=http://www.podiumcafe.com/book-corner/2016/8/21/12573418/the-end-of-the-road-by-alasdair-fotheringham| title=The End of the Road Review| publisher=Podium Caf\u00e9}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fotheringham, Alasdair}}\n[[Category:Cycling journalists]]\n[[Category:British male journalists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{UK-journalist-stub}}\n{{UK-cycling-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alasdair_Fotheringham"}
